  "summary": "The paper investigates the scaling properties of encoder-decoder Transformer models in Neural Machine Translation (NMT), proposing a novel bivariate scaling law that models cross-entropy loss as a function of both encoder and decoder sizes. It rigorously demonstrates that model scaling behavior and the correlation between cross-entropy loss and generation quality (BLEU/BLEURT) are acutely influenced by \"composition bias\" (Source-Original vs. Target-Original test data). The authors find that decoder scaling is generally more effective for reducing cross-entropy loss and that BLEU scores can deteriorate for source-original data despite continuous loss improvements.",
